# **8. Non-Functional Requirements**

| **Requirement** | **Description** | **Priority** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Mobile responsive | Interface must fully work on smartphones. Soltanmyrat works from the warehouse with a phone. Greenhouse managers enter data from tablets. | High |
| Weak internet | Greenhouses may have unstable internet. System must handle connection loss and save data on reconnection. | Medium |
| Multilingual | Interface in 2 languages: Turkmen, Russian. Reference data in all languages (RU/EN/TM confirmed in firm data). | High |
| Security | JWT auth. Every action tied to a user. Audit log. Data is never deleted, only marked inactive. | High |
| Performance | Table of 1,959+ shipments must load in < 3 seconds. Filtering/sorting < 1 second. | Medium |
| Data import | Import historical data from current Excel files (1,959 shipments, 111 import firms, 24 export firms, 2,014 truck/drivers, 31 contracts, 1,557 price entries). | High (for launch) |
| Notifications | Web + SMS notifications for: status change, overdue report, 13:00 deadline approach, shipment change after advance. | Medium |
| Integration | Read from Logo Tiger ERP (accounting). Link to existing Trip Management system for vehicle/driver data. Future: GPS via Navixy. | Phases 3-4 |
| Deployment | On company server (no cloud). Docker containers. | High |
| Parallel operation | First 2 weeks after launch — simultaneous work in old Excel and new system for verification. | High |
| API-first design | All functionality exposed via REST API to enable future mobile CRM for field operations (sales reps, drivers, inspectors). | High |

# **9. Implementation Phases**

4 phases of 3 weeks each = 12 weeks to MVP.

| **Phase** | **Weeks** | **What must work by the end of the phase** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1. Foundation | 1-3 | Auth. Import 1,959 shipments + 111 import firms + 24 export firms + 2,014 truck/drivers + 31 contracts. Shipment list with filters. Shipment detail (view only). References (blocks, firms, customers, products) loaded. Firm document portal (basic). |
| 2. Lifecycle | 4-6 | Create new shipment. Transition through 13 statuses with validations. Firm assignment. Block source entry. Kanban board. Sales report form. Overdue reports list. Comments. Quality inspection. Finansist advances. Electronic document submission to depo. |
| 3. Planning | 7-9 | Weekly planning (15x6 grid). Truck forecast. Quotas (24 firms, government per-firm). Dashboard with KPIs. Block summary. Domestic sales. Price panel (1,557 entries). Contract management. Gapy Satysh portal. |
| 4. Polish | 10-12 | Role-based access (12 roles). Audit log. Notifications. Mobile adaptation. Data validation. Settings. API documentation for future mobile CRM. Training (3 sessions). Parallel operation (2 weeks). |

## **9.1 Acceptance Criteria**

| **Criterion** | **How to verify** | **Who verifies** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| All data correct | Gadam confirms: 'I see my shipments and data is correct' | Gadam |
| Roles work | Log in as each role — only own fields/functions visible | Data Analyst |
| No critical bugs | Run 10 typical work scenarios without failures | Data Analyst |
| Works on phone | Test on Gadam's phone and Soltanmyrat's tablet | Gadam, Soltanmyrat |
| Documented | Brief changelog (5-10 lines) per phase | Developer |
| API documented | REST endpoints documented for mobile CRM handoff | Developer |